FBIS3-26582 "drchi027_n_94024" FBIS-CHI-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 Economic & Agricultural Grain Output Reaches Record 456 Million Tons OW0702062594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0615 GMT 7 Feb 94 OW0702062594 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, February 7 (XINHUA) -- In 1993 China's total grain output hit a record 456.4 million tons, despite the fact that the total grain area had shrunk over the previous few years. The figure means that the total grain production increased by 50 percent in three leaps between 1979 and 1993. The country's total grain output was 300 million tons in 1979, 354.5 million tons in 1982, 407.3 million tons in 1984, and 456.4 million tons in 1993. According to analyses done by foreign economists, out of every extra 50 kg of grain harvested worldwide between 1980 and 1991 20 kg were increased in China.
